# GPX Standardiser

Club CLI to copy GPX files under a canonical basename pattern:

- Filename pattern and limits: [`docs/adr/0002-filename-format.md`](docs/adr/0002-filename-format.md)
- Metrics: [`docs/adr/0003-gpx-metrics-calculation.md`](docs/adr/0003-gpx-metrics-calculation.md)
- CLI and paths: [`docs/adr/0005-cli-and-output-workflow.md`](docs/adr/0005-cli-and-output-workflow.md)
- Coverage: [`docs/adr/0006-test-coverage.md`](docs/adr/0006-test-coverage.md)

## Rules

- Do not hardcode `inbound-files` / `outbound-files` in code behaviour; callers pass `--route-files`, a positional `.gpx` path, and `--output-folder`.
- Production flow **copies** renamed files only; never modify source GPXs in place.
- Internal GPX `<name>` should be description-only (`docs/adr/0004-description-and-metadata.md`).
- Use **uv** for dependencies and **`uv run pytest`** / **`pytest-cov`** per ADR-0001 and ADR-0006.

Keep scope narrow: CLI only for local files; no third-party uploads API integration.
